'''''Better Living Through Criticism''''' is a book by [[A. O. Scott]] on the societal role of criticism.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/04/books/review-in-better-living-through-criticism-ao-scott-offers-insight.html|title=Review : In Better Living Through Criticism AO Scott Offers Insight|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Smallwood |first=Christine |url=https://harpers.org/archive/2016/02/258903/?single=1 |title=[Reviews&#93; &#124; New Books, by Christine Smallwood &#124; Harper's Magazine |website=Harpers.org |date= |accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Review by Jonathan Derbyshire |url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/f211b576-e139-11e5-9217-6ae3733a2cd1.html |title=‘Better Living Through Criticism: How to Think About Art, Pleasure, Beauty, and Truth’, by AO Scott |website=FT.com |date=2016-03-04 |accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/books/la-ca-jc-scott-criticism-20160221-story.html |title=Film critic A.O. Scott's book 'Better Living Through Criticism' is reviewed by art critic Dan Fox, who asks, Criticism - what is it good for? |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date= |accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Rodriguezrrodriguez |first=Rene |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/entertainment/books/article61264172.html |title=Review: A.O. Scott’s ‘Better Living Through Criticism’ and Owen Gleiberman’s ‘Movie Freak’ |newspaper=[[Miami Herald]] |date=2016-02-19 |accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=James Adams |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/books-and-media/book-reviews/review-in-better-living-through-criticism-ao-scott-mounts-a-defence-of-his-profession/article28744094/ |title=Review: In Better Living Through Criticism, A.O. Scott mounts a defence of his profession |newspaper=[[The Globe and Mail]] |date=2016-02-12 |accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2016/03/ao-scott-critic-without-a-cause/426828/ |title=Review: ‘Better Living Through Criticism: How to Think About Art, Pleasure, Beauty, and Truth’ by A. O. Scott |newspaper=[[The Atlantic]] |date= |accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Miller |first=Laura |url=http://www.slate.com/articles/arts/books/2016/01/a_o_scott_s_better_living_through_criticism_reviewed.html |title=A.O. Scott’s Better Living Through Criticism, reviewed |website=Slate.com |date=2016-01-31 |accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/2016/2/24/11102592/better-living-through-criticism-review-ao-scott |title=Film critic A.O. Scott’s new book is an artful guide to how criticism works |website=Vox.com |date= |accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Betancourt |first=Manuel |url=https://lareviewofbooks.org/review/whose-criticism-on-a-o-scotts-better-living-through-criticism |title=Whose Criticism? On A. O. Scott’s "Better Living Through Criticism" - Los Angeles Review of Books |website=Lareviewofbooks.org |date=2016-02-08 |accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bookforum.com/inprint/022_05/15599 |title=Critical Condition - bookforum.com / current issue |website=Bookforum.com |date= |accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-1-59420-483-8 |title=Nonfiction Book Review: Better Living Through Criticism: How to Think About Art, Pleasure, Beauty, and Truth |author=A.O. Scott |publisher=[[Penguin Press]] |isbn=978-1-59420-483-8 |website=Publishersweekly.com |date=2015-11-23 |accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2016/03/07/critics-in-the-age-of-opinion |title=Says You |newspaper=[[The New Yorker]] |date=2016-03-07 |accessdate=2016-05-13}}</ref>

